'''Fay David''' was the art department supervisor for [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']]. Additionally, she was previously a visual effects producer in for [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]. She played one of [[Padmé Amidala|Queen Amidala's]] handmaidens in one of the final scenes in ''The Phantom Menace'' and replaced [[Mary Oyaya]] as [[Luminara Unduli]] in ''Revenge of the Sith''<ref name="Star Wars: The Lightsaber Collection" /> in a brief cameo. In ''Attack of the Clones'', she stood in for [[Orli Shoshan]] as [[Shaak Ti]] in the Jedi Archives scene. [[Clone Commander]] "[[Faie]]" is named after David.<ref name="Neyo DB>{{DB|character|commanderneyo|Neyo, Commander}}</ref>

